<HEADLINE> Khatami Meets With Iraqi Foreign Minister </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, January 21 (Xinhua) -- Iranian President Mohammad
Khatami Wednesday met with visiting Iraqi Foreign Minister
Mohammed Saeed al-Sahhaf.
</P>
<P>
Al-Sahhaf briefed Khatami on the current situation in Iraq and
the negotiations between Iraq and the U.N. over arms inspection,
the Iranian official news agency IRNA reported.
</P>
<P>
The Iraqi foreign minister arrived here Friday night for a
three-day official visit. But the visit was extended hours before
al-Sahhaf decided to leave.
</P>
<P>
Local observers believed that one of the objectives of
al-Sahhaf's visit to Iran was to seek Iran's help in lifting the
U.N. sanctions imposed on Baghdad for its invasion of Kuwait
in 1990.
</P>
<P>
Iraq believes that Iran, the present chairman of the
Organization of the Islamic Conference (OIC), can play an
important role in encouraging the Islamic countries to put more
pressures on the U.N. to lift the embargo and to defend Iraq'
rights, diplomats here said.
</P>
<P>
They said that Iran and Iraq have also shown their willingness
to improve their cool relations in order to challenge their common
enemy the United States.
</P>
<P>
During al-Sahhaf's visit, Iran and Iraq reached an agreement to
form two committees to solve remaining disputes between the two
countries.
</P>
<P>
The two committees will discuss the issues of prisoners of war
(POW) left over by the 1980-88 Iran-Iraq war, commercial
cooperation between Iran and Iraq on the basis of the
U.N. Security Council resolutions and travel of Iranian and Iraqi
citizens to either country.
</P>
<P>
The agreement was considered as a constructive step taken by
the two governments to improve their relations, since the issue of
POWs was believed to be the major hurdle for their rapprochement.
</P>
</TEXT>
