<HEADLINE> Chinese Counsellors Praised For Suggestions </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 21 (Xinhua) -- Chinese vice premier Wu Bangguo
gave high credits to the State Council counsellors who have made
valuable suggestions to government work and its major decisions.
</P>
<P>
Wu made the remark at a New Year reception held here today for
the members of the Counsellors' Office under the State Council and
the Central Research Institute of Culture and History.
</P>
<P>
Wu said the counsellors have offered suggestions to the annual
government report and to draft laws and regulations and a great
many of their ideas have been adopted by the central government.
</P>
<P>
The Vice-Premier expressed his thanks to the counsellors for
their contributions to the country's reunification cause. 
</P>
</TEXT>
