<HEADLINE> Belarussian President Arrives in MOSCOW </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, January 21 (Xinhua) -- Belarussian President Alexander
Lukashenko arrived here on Wednesday to attend the session of the
Supreme Council of the Russian-Belarussian Union, according to the
Itar-Tass news agency.
</P>
<P>
The Supreme Council will focus on the Union budget for 1998
which was approved by its executive committee.
</P>
<P>
The Russian and Belarussian sides are expected to discuss the
problem of coordinated actions in the sphere of foreign policy, a
purpose-oriented program for combating organized crime and a
concept of a coordinated defense policy, the report said.
</P>
<P>
During the stay in Moscow Lukashenko will also take part in the
session of the Inter-State Council of Belarussia, Russia,
Kazakhstan and Kyrgyzstan.
</P>
<P>
He is to meet with Russian Prime Minister Viktor Chernomyrdin,
Kazakh President Nursultan Nazarbayev and Moscow Mayor Yuri
Luzhkov.
</P>
<P>
It said that on Thursday morning Lukashenko will have a
30-minute tete-a-tete meeting with Russian President Boris
Yeltsin.
</P>
<P>
The meeting will be followed by sessions in the Kremlin of the
Supreme Council of the Union of Belarussia and Russia. 
</P>
</TEXT>
