<HEADLINE> Wholesale Trade Down Slightly in November </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, January 21 (Xinhua) -- Canadian wholesalers sold 24.8
billion dollars (16.1 billion USD) worth of goods and service in
November 1997, down 0.8 percent from October, Statistics Canada
said Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Led by farm machinery, household goods, and apparel and dry
goods, nine of the 11 trade groups showed lower sales, the
statistics agency said.
</P>
<P>
In the meantime, wholesale sales of computers and electronic
equipment, and motor vehicles and parts were up slightly.
</P>
<P>
The agency noted that in general, Canada's wholesale sales have
been increasing since January 1996, after a slowdown in demand for
most of 1995.
</P>
<P>
So far, the year of 1997 has been an excellent year for
Canadian wholesalers. Sales for the first 11 months of 1997 were
12.5 percent higher than in the same period in 1996. 
</P>
</TEXT>
