<HEADLINE> McDonald's Sale in France Increases in 1997 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, January 21 (Xinhua) -- The American fast food
corporation Mcdonald's sold 8.389 billion francs (1.4 billion U.S.
dollars) of products in France in 1997, a 19 percent rise over
1996, Agence France-Presse quoted the management of the
corporation as saying on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Mcdonald's, which kept losing money in the first 15 years of
its running in France until 1994, now has 630 restaurants in the
country and plans to open 70 to 80 more in 1998, said Denis
Hennequin, the president of Mcdonald's France.
</P>
<P>
Mcdonald's also created 2,000 jobs in France in 1997, including
400 full-time jobs. Its staff in France totaled 27,000.
</P>
<P>
It is not known how much profit Mcdonald's makes each year in
France.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
