<HEADLINE> Nestle's Sales in 1997 Reach 46 Billion Dollars </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, January 21 (Xinhua) -- The Nestle Group's consolidated
sales in 1997 reached 69.9 billion Swiss francs (about 46 billion
US dollars), an increase of nearly 16 percent over the preceding
year.
</P>
<P>
Nestle assumed that the 1997 net profit growth rate will be
similar to the growth rate of sales. According to a press release
issued today by the Nestle S.A. at its headquarters in Vevey.
</P>
<P>
Real internal growth accelerated from 2.7 percent in 1996 to
3.2 percent for the full year 1997. It was particularly strong in
the Middle East, eastern Europe, many Asian markets and North
America.
</P>
<P>
As the Swiss franc devalued against the US dollar, exchange
rates had a positive impact of 8.1 percent.
</P>
<P>
Full results for 1997 and the dividend proposal will be
released following the meeting of the Board of Directors of Nestle
SA on March 26, 1998. 
</P>
</TEXT>
