<HEADLINE> Siemens, 3Com Cooperate to Integrate Telephone with </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, January 21 (Xinhua) -- Germany's Siemens AG announced
Wednesday that it is working together with the U.S. 3Com
Corporation to launch in spring this year a new technology to
integrate telephone with the Internet.
</P>
<P>
Siemens said that the new technology, which incorporates 3Com's
remote data access technology with the EWSD digital switching
system of Siemens, would allow telephone network operators to
offer their customers efficient Internet access via existing
telephone switching systems without needing to set up additional
new Internet infrastructures.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, combined with the new technology, Siemens is also
developing new Internet services which would make it possible for
customers who are surfing the Internet to identify incoming
telephone calls or to display their telephone account on their PC
screens.
</P>
<P>
Siemens said that it expected about 300 million German marks
(about 160 million U.S. dollars) in extra sales from this product
innovation by the year 2000. 
</P>
</TEXT>
