<HEADLINE> French Glass Giant Plans to Invest 263 Mln Dollars </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, January 22 (Xinhua) -- French glass manufacturing
giant Saint Gobain plans to invest more than 263.85 million U.S.
dollars in India over the next three to five years to take
advantage of the growing demand for glass, ceramics and abrasives.
</P>
<P>
"We are committed to India in the long-term and we will bring
in all our business divisions in Tamil Nadu of southern India in
the next few years," said Jacques Achenbroich, president of Saint
Gobain's flat glass division, on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Achenbroich was speaking at the ground-breaking ceremony of a
118.73 million dollar glass project at Sriperumbudur near Chennai,
capital of Tamil Nadu.
</P>
<P>
The project would go on stream in December 1999 and commercial
production would start in early 2000. St. Gobain has tied up raw
material supply with several Tamil Nadu government agencies and
all the inputs would be sourced from within the country, he said.
</P>
<P>
The company plans to invest another 118.73 million dollars in
the second phase of the Sriperumbudur project, in about five years
from now, he added.  
</P>
