<HEADLINE> Agassi Beats Costa to Return Form </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, January 22 (Xinhua) -- Former world No.1 Andre Agassi
won a fourth-set battle of wills in Melbourne Wednesday against
Spaniard Albert Costa to maintain his return to form at the
Australian Open tennis tournament.
</P>
<P>
Agassi displayed some excellent court coverage and
groundstrokes and eventually disposed of the 16th seed 6-4, 6-4,
2-6, 7-5 in two hours and 26 minutes.
</P>
<P>
Agassi, who spent much of last year on the sidelines to slip
out of the top 100 for the first time since turning professional
in 1986, looked to be home when he broke serve to go 4-2 up in the
fourth.
</P>
<P>
But the emotional Spaniard, frequently yelling to himself and
waving his arms after any poor shot, refused to give up and soon
broke back and held serve to level the set at 4-4.
</P>
<P>
Games then went to serve until Agassi broke again to win.
</P>
<P>
Earlier Wednesday, Costa's compatriot Arantxa Sanchez Vicario
gave Russian Elena Makarova a 6-0, 6-0 tennis lesson. 
</P>
