trade, budget, foreign policy and defense, adopted Thursday
several documents, including the Union's budget for 1998, as well
as procedures for passing and implementing resolutions of the
Union's Supreme Council and Executive Committee.
</P>
<P>
The Council passed documents on coordinated foreign policy in
1998 and 1999, on the concept of a joint defense policy, and on a
joint program for combating organized crime to the year 2000.
</P>
<P>
Yeltsin also reached agreement with visiting Belarus President
Alexander Lukashenko that the main task for their Union this year
is integration, primarily in economies. 
