<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, January 22 (Xinhua) -- The NATO-led multinational
Stabilization Force (SFOR) Thursday detained a Bosnian Serb war
crimes suspect in Bosnia, the western military alliance announced
here.
</P>
<P>
The war crimes suspect, identified as Goran Jelisic, has been
indicted by the International Criminal Tribunal for former
Yugoslavia for the murder of more than 16 people, torture, theft,
plunder and ordering the murder of many others.
</P>
<P>
There were no casualties sustained during the action that
resulted following the identification of Jelisic on the streets of
Bijeljina.
</P>
<P>
The action was taken in accordance with SFOR's mandate which
authorizes it to detain persons indicted for war crimes when
encountered in the course of its duties.
</P>
<P>
The detained is being processed for immediate transfer to the
Hague, where the tribunal is seated. 
