steered out of the difficulties.
</P>
<P>
The PIA, the state-owned national flag carrier, which was
graded as one of the top 10 airlines in the world in the
1960s-70s, is now ranked as 41st among 240 carriers of the world
as its profitability has registered a decline during the past
years.  
