world, with the number in China increasing every year.
</P>
<P>
Medical experts agree that bone marrow transplants provide an
efficient method of treating leukemia. However, a sufficient
number of volunteers are required to increase the victims' chances
of survival.
</P>
<P>
Donations to the Bone Marrow Donor Bank of China in Beijing has
remained slow, with only 3,000 prospective donors by the end of
1997. 
