<HEADLINE> Jiang Zemin Calls for Advancement of Anti-corruption Campaign (3) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Leading officials should be strict with their spouses and
children, preventing them from abusing official power and
influence, correcting their wrongdoings in time and not shielding
their law-breaking activities, Jiang said.
</P>
<P>
In addition to proceeding with reform, opening-up and economic
growth, Jiang said, leading officials within the range of their
administrations should play key roles in improving the Party's
work style, building clean government and combating corruption.
</P>
<P>
Jiang pointed out that better Party and government work and
anti-corruption efforts require law-enforcement contingents which
are politically trustworthy and competent.
</P>
<P>
Current law-enforcement contingents are good who, in the fight
against corruption, are able to conscientiously carry out the
policies and assignments of the CPC central committee and
safeguard the interest of the nation and the people, Jiang said.
</P>
<P>
He urged law-enforcement personnel to have a strong political
awareness, fairness and honesty, a high sense of discipline,
professional competence and a fine work style.
</P>
<P>
Jiang explained that strong political awareness means being in
agreement with the Party Central Committee, and adhering to the
Party's basic theory and line, and its principles and policies.
Fairness and honesty requires law-enforcement people to put
priority on the interests of the nation and the people, handle
things justly and not be swayed by personal considerations.
</P>
<P>
As to the sense of discipline, law-enforcement people must
abide by laws and regulations in an exemplary way and resist
temptation.
</P>
<P>
In addition, they should improve their professional knowledge
to increase efficiency, and they should keep close contacts with
the masses and serve the people heart and soul, Jiang said.
</P>
