<HEADLINE> Shanghai Plans to Accelerate Building of Modern Financial System </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, January 22 (Xinhua) -- Shanghai plans to speed up the
building of a modern financial system to become a financial center
in the Asia-Pacific region.
</P>
<P>
At the annual financial work conference here today, Mao
Yingliang, president of the Shanghai branch of the People's Bank
of China, said the east China metropolis will implement its
financial reforms in a well-planned way to attain its goal.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai will steadily develop the capital market by expanding
direct fund-raising, and develop the monetary market to promote
trans-regional fund flow, Mao said.
</P>
<P>
While continuing to implement a relatively stringent monetary
policy, he said, Shanghai will improve its financial controls by
abolishing limits on loans for agricultural projects, reforms of
state-owned enterprises, marketable housing schemes, development
of the Pudong New Area and high-tech businesses.
</P>
<P>
He added that Shanghai will increase supervision over and enact
more regulations on the operation of financial institutions.
</P>
