<TEXT>
<P>
SHIJIAZHUANG, January 22 (Xinhua) -- Thousands of people
attended a ceremony held here today to commemorate a Canadian
doctor who gave his life to the Chinese people's anti-fascism
cause 59 years ago.
</P>
<P>
Sent by the Communist Party in Canada and the United States,
Dr. Norman Bethune led a medical team to China in 1938 to help
the Chinese people in the war of resistance against Japan.
</P>
<P>
