<HEADLINE> China Cracks Down on Seismic Design of High-Rise Buildings </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 22 (Xinhua) -- China will begin cracking down
on seismic design this year to improve earthquake safety in the
country's high-rise buildings exceeding 120 meters.
</P>
<P>
More than 300 high-rise buildings have gone up nationwide in
the last years because of rapid economic development and urban
construction, Ye Rutang, vice minister of construction, said here
today.
</P>
<P>
A survey of seismic designs in a dozen cities revealed many
hidden problems in these high-rise buildings, he said.
</P>
<P>
To improve the reliability and earthquake safety of these
designs, the Ministry of Construction has issued provisional
administrative rules for high-rise structures and set strict
standards for design institutes to follow. 
</P>
