<HEADLINE> 400 S.Leoneans Killed by Kamajor Militia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FREETOWN, January 22 (Xinhua) -- Over 400 civilians were
killed by Kamajor militiamen last weekend in Siera Leone's
eastern Town of Tongo Field, State Radio reported Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The disclosure was made at a meeting of paramount chiefs ands
tribal heads in Bo, the country's second largest city in the
south, said the radio.
</P>
<P>
The meeting described the Kamajor massacre as "unprecedented"
and called on the authorities "to prevent a recurrence".
</P>
<P>
"The kamajors should remember that Sierra Leoneans are one
people and in the interest of peace, the various tribes sbould
always operate under a peaceful atmosphere and avoid trivalism,"
the radio said.
</P>
<P>
There has not been any independent confirmation of the 400
civilians' deaths and the army has still not disclosed casualty
figures.
</P>
<P>
Humanitarian agencies said they are worried over the mass
exods of people fleeing "vulnerable areas" in the south and east
of the country.
</P>
<P>
"We were not expecting such massive upsurge of people and we
are finding it difficult to cope in providing adequate food and
medicines for them," a Red Cross official said in Freetown.
</P>
<P>
Relief officials said they would have to embark on "cross
border operations" from neighbouring Guinea to augment their
humanitarian stock. 
</P>
