<HEADLINE> Jiang Zemin Calls for Advancement of Anti-Corruption Campaign (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 22 (Xinhua) -- President Jiang Zemin today
called on leading officials at various levels to raise their
competence at work and guard against corruption.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the Second Plenary Session of the Central
Commission of the Communist Party of China (CPC) for Discipline
Inspection, Jiang said these efforts are being made to unify the
Party's concern with the people's aspirations in their advancement
of building socialism with Chinese characteristics.
</P>
<P>
Jiang, also general secretary of the CPC Central Committee,
explained that the top task for the Party and the country at
present is to hold high the banner of the Deng Xiaoping Theory,
further emancipate minds, seek truth from facts, seize the
opportunity, focus on economic construction and strive to make
breakthroughs in economic restructuring.
</P>
<P>
Li Peng, Qiao Shi, Zhu Rongji, Li Ruihuan, Hu Jintao, Li
Lanqing and other Chinese leaders attended the session presided
over by Wei Jianxing, secretary of the Central Commission for
Discipline Inspection.
</P>
<P>
Jiang pointed out that the improvement of the Party's work
style, building a clean government and waging the anti-corruption
struggle are important parts of the Deng Xiaoping Theory, and an
inevitable requirement posed by the building of socialism with
Chinese characteristics.
</P>
<P>
Since the 14th National Party Congress, a number of major
corruption cases have been ferreted out and the campaign to
practice the economy and curb extravagance has been launched. The
Party and government departments have scored great successes in
this regard, he said.
</P>
<P>
Jiang stressed that the anti-corruption struggle is a long and
arduous task which requires effective measures.
</P>
<P>
He pointed out that to solve the new problems in the country's
opening-up and modernization drive, the most important thing is to
keep close contacts between the Party and the people, and to rely
on the people.
</P>
<P>
Jiang said he believes that as long those close contacts are
maintained, even the biggest and most complicated problems can be
solved.
</P>
</TEXT>
