<HEADLINE> Jiang Zemin Calls For Advancement of Anti-Corruption Campaign (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Jiang said the Party will continue to work hard to build an
honest and clean government in the new year, and at the same time
carry out tasks concerned with the reform, opening-up and
stability.
</P>
<P>
In combating corruption, he emphasized adherence to unified
leadership of the Party committees at each level, joint effort of
the Party and the government, as well as the participation and
support of the people.
</P>
<P>
These are important steps to effectively stop and punish
corruption, and should continue to be implemented, he added.
</P>
<P>
He pointed out that the work to foster clean and
self-disciplined officials must be firmly grasped, that each
stipulation on combating waste and extravagant spending must be
carried out to the letter, and that some major and vital cases
concerned with severe violations of the law and discipline must be
looked into thoroughly.
</P>
<P>
Jiang also called on related departments to reduce the burden
on farmers and enterprises and to check funds exceeding the
financial budget, while at the same time firmly rectifying
unhealthy tendencies of some departments and lines of business as
well as protecting against officials infringing on people's rights
and interests.
</P>
<P>
Jiang required officials at each level to act as models in the
anti-corruption campaign, and to carry forward the fine tradition
of working hard and living frugally.
</P>
<P>
At present, officials should care more about the laid-off
workers, needy employees of the state-owned enterprises and people
in impoverished areas, he said.
</P>
