<HEADLINE> France Hails Arrest of Serb War Criminal Suspect in Bosnia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, January 22 (Xinhua) -- France Thursday hailed the arrest
of Goran Jelisic, a Serb war criminal suspect, by American troops
serving in the Stabilization Force (SFOR) in Bijeljina, northeast
Bosnia.
</P>
<P>
"We are delighted at this operation. For France, the war
criminals should take account of their actions in front of the
International Penal Tribunal (in the Hague)," said French Foreign
Ministry spokesman Yves Doutriaux.
</P>
<P>
A SFOR spokesman announced Thursday morning in Sarajevo that
Jelisic was arrested in a bloodiless operation carried out by SFOR
force in Bijeljina.
</P>
<P>
SFOR is transferring him to the Hague, where the International
Penal Tribunal in charge of hearing war crimes in former
Yugoslavia is located.
</P>
<P>
Jelisic is charged with genocide, crimes against humanity and
grave violations of the Geneva Conventions when he served as the
chief of a concentration camp in Luka near Brcko in northeast
Bosnia during the war in Bonsia. 
</P>
</TEXT>
