<HEADLINE> Cape Verde Strives to Develop Telecommunications </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, January 22 (Xinhua) -- After being privatized in 1996,
Cape Verde Telecom has invested more than 14 million U.S. Dollars
annually in the development of national telecommunications
systems, the Angolan News Agency reported today.
</P>
<P>
Eugenio Inocencio, General Manager of Cape Verde Telecom, said
at a news briefing on the opening of his country's cellular
telephone network today that rapid progress has been made in
developing the telecommunications sector in the past two years.
</P>
<P>
He said that in 1996, the first year of the privatization
process, the number of telephones in the country surpassed 5,000.
And the figure reached 9,000 and Internet was also introduced
into Cape Verde in 1997, he added.
</P>
<P>
Inocencio attributed the progress to privatization and foreign
investment in the country.
</P>
<P>
It is necessary to put high investment into the
telecommunications industry for the improvement of communication
conditions which are vital for attracting foreign investors, he
noted.
</P>
<P>
Cape Verde is composed of over 10 islands in the Atlantic
Ocean, with a population of 61,000. Tecommunications development
will facilitate contacts among its islanders and promote
its economic growth. 
</P>
</TEXT>
