<HEADLINE> CPPCC to Convene Ninth National Committee In March </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 22 (Xinhua) -- The First Session of the Ninth
National Committee of the Chinese People's Political Consultative
Conference (CPPCC) will be held beginning March 3, 1998.
</P>
<P>
The decision was made by the 23th meeting of the Standing
Committee of the Eighth CPPCC National Committee that concluded
here today.
</P>
<P>
It was suggested at the meeting that the forthcoming Ninth
CPPCC National Committee examines the work report by the Standing
Committee of the Eighth CPPCC National Committee, elects the Ninth
CPPCC chairman, vice chairmen, secretary-general and observes the
first meeting of the Ninth National People's Congress.
</P>
<P>
CPPCC holds a term of five years.
</P>
<P>
The Ninth CPPCC will have 2,196 members, or some 100 more over
the previous. The number of members from Hong Kong Special
Administrative Region, Macao and Taiwan is the biggest, compared
with the previous ones.
</P>
<P>
Addressing today's closing session, CPPCC Chairman Li Ruihuan
said that over the past 50 years, CPPCC has scored great
achievements, accumulated rich experience and lessons.
</P>
<P>
He pointed out that the Eighth CPPCC is about to have its
historical mission fulfilled soon. The Ninth CPPCC will be
responsible to push its cause into the 21st century.
</P>
<P>
"It is our hope that the new national committee of the CPPCC
will lose no time to carry out the plans worked out by the Eighth
CPPCC, strive to solve problems and improve its work as a whole,"
Li concluded.
</P>
<P>
CPPCC vice chairman Ye Xuanping presided over today's meeting.
</P>
</TEXT>
