<HEADLINE> Zhejiang Province Improves Hotel Services </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, January 22 (Xinhua) -- East China's Zhejiang Province
has redoubled efforts and achieved notable progress in improving
hotel services in recent years.
</P>
<P>
The province's 311 hotels serving foreign tourists have 40,000
guest rooms. The figures include 100 star-rated hotels with 15,800
rooms.
</P>
<P>
Zhejiang has six four-star and 62 three-star hotels. Hotels
serving foreign tourists generated earnings of 4.3 billion yuan
and recorded net profits of 270 million yuan.
</P>
<P>
The province ranks fifth in China in terms of various indices
for the nation's hotel industry, according to local tourism
officials.
</P>
<P>
The Zhejiang Tourism Administration has announced plans to
upgrade all hotels handling foreign tourists into star-rated
facilities over the next five years. 
</P>
