<HEADLINE> China to Further Support for Machinery Exporters </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 22 (Xinhua) -- The Export-Import Bank of China
(EximBank) is expected to grant intensified its support for the
nation's machinery and electronics products manufacturers to
achieve a steady growth in their export, according to a decision
of the bank.
</P>
<P>
High-tech and profitable products such as vessels, sets of
machinery, telecommunications and electronics goods will continue
to get the priority support from the policy bank, said Tong
Zhiguang, the board chairman of the EximBank.
</P>
<P>
Joint-stock enterprises and overseas-funded but
China-controlled ventures will also begin to receive the bank's
financing this year, according to Tong Zhiguang.
</P>
<P>
The bank is also considering further lowering the interest rate
of the policy loans, in a bid to reduce the production cost of the
Chinese enterprises and thereby enhance its competitiveness in the
international market.
</P>
<P>
Set up as a policy bank to finance the export of capital goods
mainly comprising machinery and electronics products, the bank has
approved a total of more than 40 billion yuan and 224 million US
dollars in export credit since 1994, helping achieving an export
profit of 11 billion US dollars, said Tong.
</P>
<P>
It also provided guarantee for 4.4 billion US dollars' worth of
electronics and machinery products, and sets of equipment during
the period.
</P>
<P>
The bank is expected to increase policy loans to Chinese
enterprises setting up branches and contracting projects overseas,
to bolster the export of machinery and electronics products,
according to the board chairman of the EximBank.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the bank will also expand the export credit
insurance sector to help the Chinese businesses hedge risks and
win more international biddings.  
</P>
</TEXT>
