<HEADLINE> China Issues New Policy on Agro-Science Development </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 22 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese government issued
today its new policy on development of agricultural science for
the next 13 years.
</P>
<P>
Chinese scientists and technicians of agro-science are urged to
improve rapidly the research and development capacity and manage
to have China's agro-science research rank the world front level
by the year 2010.
</P>
<P>
Chinese agro scientists are also called for paying more efforts
on spreading scientific discoveries in agriculture.
</P>
<P>
The new policy stressed the country's agro-high-tech
development to encourage the technical upgrading in agricultural
field.
</P>
<P>
The new policy called on application of more bio-scientific
discoveries in farming and establishment of internationalized
agro-information system.
</P>
<P>
According to the policy, major efforts are also expected in
application of marine science, space technology, nuclear
technology and remote sensing in agriculture.
</P>
<P>
The new policy drafted by 10 ministries and departments
including the State Science and Technology Commission (SSTC),
State Planning Commission and Chinese Academy of Sciences.
</P>
<P>
The policy stipulates the building of more model modernized
farming zones to lead the overall agro-development.
</P>
<P>
An official with the SSTC said that the new policy was based on
China's 1985 policy on agriculture after remending and increasing
large amount of high-tech contents.  
</P>
</TEXT>
