<HEADLINE> Guangzhou Railway Station Busy Handling Holiday-makers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, January 22 (Xinhua) -- It is expected that over
100,000 passengers will leave Guangzhou by train everyday in the
next few days to head back home for the traditional Spring
Festival which falls on February 28.
</P>
<P>
Yesterday, the departing passengers at the Guangzhou Railway
Station rocketed to 106,000, over 10,000 more than the figure
recorded the previous day, and a rise of 26 percent as compared
with the same period of the previous year. To cope with the
crowds, the station added 35 temporary trains.
</P>
<P>
In the first 14 days after the Spring Festival transportation
began, the station, which is one of the busiest in China, has
already handled 931,000 departing passengers, a year-on-year rise
of 14.9 percent.
</P>
<P>
The station has to add a total of 296 pairs of trains to deal
with the situation, which is 57 pairs more than last year's
figure. 
</P>
