<HEADLINE> First Capacity-Extended Optic Fiber Communication System Opens </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, January 22 (Xinhua) -- China's first
capacity-extended optic fibre communication system has already
passed the appraisal and gone into operation between Guangzhou and
Shenzhen, two cities in south China's Guangdong Province.
</P>
<P>
Experts here said the wave-length division multiplexing (WDM)
optical fibre communication system could expand the communication
capacity several times to several dozens of times without making
any technical upgrading of the existing optic fibre lines.
</P>
<P>
Guangzhou is 150 kilometers from Shenzhen.
</P>
<P>
The system was developed by Beijing University and produced by
Shenzhen Information Highway Photoelectric Communication Co.
</P>
<P>
Experts here believed that the system will help increase the
capacity of optic fibre lines in China without putting much
investment.  
</P>
