<HEADLINE> Nigeria Names Political Detainees to Be Freed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, January 22 (Xinhua) -- The Nigerian authorities have
worked out a list of political detainees to be released once it
is approved by Head of State Sani Abacha.
</P>
<P>
Chairman of the National Human Rights Commission, Justice Paul
Nwokedi, made the disclosure Wednesday in the Nigerian capital
Abuja, after a closed-door meeting with Inspector-general of
police, Alhaji Ibrahim Coomassie.
</P>
<P>
Nwokedi told the press after the meeting that arrangements for
the release are almost completed and that once the list is
approved by General Abacha, the political detainees will be
freed.
</P>
<P>
In a national broadcast marking his fourth anniversary in
power, Abacha announced last November that political detainees
whose release will no longer pose threat to national security
will be freed.
</P>
<P>
Among Nigeria's eminent political detainees are Chief M.K.O.
Abiola, the acclaimed winner of the nullified June 12, 1993
presidential election, former head of state, General Olusegun
Obasanjo and others for involvement in the alleged botched coup
of 1995, and a number of union leaders and journalists. 
