<DOCNO> XIE19980122.0116 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-01-22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> HK's CPI Drops Slightly in December </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, January 22 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong's Composite
Consumer Price Index (CPI) showed a year-on-year increase of 5.2
percent in December last year, compared with 5.4 percent the
previous month, the Census and Statistics Department said on
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The Composite CPI is compiled on the basis of the combined
expenditure patter of households covered by three sub-indices.
</P>
<P>
The CPI (A) rose by 4.8 percent last December on a year-on-year
basis, as against 5.1 percent in November, the department said in
its latest figures.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the year-on-year increase rates of the CPI (B) and
Hang Seng CPI stood at 5.2 percent and 5.8 percent respectively,
compared with 5.4 and 5.9 percent recorded in November.
</P>
<P>
The department attributed the lower rates of increase in the
CPI (A) and CPI (B) mainly to lower rises in housing rentals.
</P>
<P>
As for the Hang Seng CPI, the slower increase was mainly due to
lower prices of outerclothing, the department said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
