<HEADLINE> Chicken Sales Up in Macao </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, January 22 (Xinhua) -- Sales of chickens have been up
again over the past week in Macao as no case of bird flu has been
detected.
</P>
<P>
The Macao Daily News reported on Thursday that chicken sales
have now surged from about 500 a day two weeks ago to more than
3,000 a day.
</P>
<P>
A Macao Health Department official said higher chicken sales
showed that local residents had regained confidence in chickens
since no bird flu case had been found here.
</P>
<P>
Normal sales of chicken are estimated at about 5,000 a day in
Macao.
</P>
<P>
Local chicken importers estimate that because of the arrival of
 Chinese Lunar New Year at the end of January, the sales are
expected to rise further. 
</P>
</TEXT>
