<HEADLINE> S. Africa Aids Tanzania on Flood Relief </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, January 22 (Xinhua) -- South Africa is sending
emergency supplies to Tanzania to relieve the situation in the
country after recent flooding and a subsequent outbreak of
Cholera there, South African Foreign Ministry said today.
</P>
<P>
A South African Air Force freighter Tuesday carried emergency
building supplies to Tanzania to help reconstruct the country's
major communication routes washed away by recent torrential
floods, the ministry said in a statement.
</P>
<P>
More building materials and a total of one million Rand (about
203,000 U.S. Dollars) of medicines will be delivered next week on
a second flight.
</P>
<P>
Part of the medicines is to help the Organization of African
Unity (OAU) to fight a cholera epidemic in Zanzibar on the
eastern coast of Tanzania, which has claimed 2,000 lives. The
rest medication will help treat displaced people in refugee camps
in the Great Lakes region. 
</P>
</TEXT>
