<HEADLINE> Stocks Fall in Tokyo on Profit-Making </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, January 22 (Xinhua) -- Tokyo stocks on Thursday suffered
the first loss in seven trading days on profit-making.
</P>
<P>
The Nikkei average of 225 selected issues on the First Section
of the Tokyo Stock Exchange dropped 278.73 points, or 1.67 percent
from Wednesday's close to 16,405.96.
</P>
<P>
The broader-based Tokyo Stock Price Index, covering all issues
on the First Section, fell 7.67 points, or 0.62 percent to
1,237.25.
</P>
<P>
Volume on the First Section came to an estimated 600 million
shares, down from Wednesday's 720.88 million shares.
</P>
<P>
NKK was Thursday's most heavily traded issue.
</P>
<P>
Traders said Thursday's drop was natural reaction after the
recent surge.
</P>
<P>
The overnight fall on Wall Street prompted selling in high-tech
issues in Tokyo, they said.
</P>
<P>
Of the 1,328 issues listed on the First Section, losers
outpaced gainers 585 to 566 with 143 issues remaining unchanged.
</P>
</TEXT>
