<DATE_TIME> 1998-01-22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 1997 Natural Disasters Kill 3,200 People in China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 22 (Xinhua) -- A civil affairs official said
here today that natural disasters in 1997 killed 3,200 people in
China and caused direct economic losses estimated at 197.5 billion
yuan (about 24 billion US dollars).
</P>
<P>
According to Li Bengong, director of the disaster relief
department under the Ministry of Civil Affairs, some 478 million
Chinese were afflicted last year by natural disasters, which
damaged 2.87 million houses and affected the harvests of over 50
million hectares of farmland.
</P>
<P>
Li noted that the major disasters hit China in 1997 include
earthquakes, droughts, hailstorms, floods, typhoon, plant
diseases, insect pests and blizzards, with quakes and droughts
doing greatest harms.
</P>
<P>
Between late January and mid April last year, Jiashi County in
northwest China's Xinjiang Uygur Autonomous Region was hit by
seven tremors beyond 6 on the Richter scale. And summer
droughts, reportedly the most serious in China since the 1970s,
ruined autumn harvests in many parts of the country.
</P>
<P>
Li pointed out that thanks to the efforts by the central and
local governments, all people afflicted by natural disasters now
have sufficient food and clothing and proper place to live, and no
major epidemics have broken out in the disaster-stricken areas.
</P>
<P>
He said that top Chinese leaders, including President Jiang
Zemin, Premier Li Peng and vice-premier Zhu Rongji, often phoned
the civil affairs ministry to learn about the disasters or went
personally to the disaster-afflicted areas to visit local people.
</P>
<P>
"All ministries and departments under the State Council have
also made every effort to help the disaster-hit areas," he added.
</P>
<P>
Last year, the ministries of civil affairs and finance jointly
allocated 2.2 billion yuan in disaster relief funds. Including
the money from local budgets and various social donations, China
in 1997 spent over 4.4 billion yuan on disaster relief.
</P>
<P>
Initial statistics showed that last year over 40 million
disaster-afflicted people received relief food, nearly 20 million
received quilts and clothes, over one million had their
disaster-caused diseases cured free of charge, and 5.11 million
were moved to safe places or resettled.
</P>
<P>
"Before the start of winter, our ministry and local governments
at all levels already helped rebuild over two million houses in
the disaster-stricken areas," Li added.
</P>
<P>
He also highly commended the role of the People's Liberation
Army (PLA), armed police force, public security personnel and
militiamen in China's disaster relief efforts last year.
</P>
<P>
Incomplete statistics from all over the country showed that in
1997, the PLA and armed police forces sent 950,000 soldiers and
officers, more than 4,400 planes and vessels and over 50,000
vehicles to participate in some 10,000 disaster relief actions,
helping rescue or move over 490,000 people. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
