<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, January 22 (Xinhua) -- A total of 193 planes took
off yesterday at Guangzhou's Baiyun Airport, transporting 28,260
passengers, thus setting a daily record for the airport.
</P>
<P>
Today, there will be a total of 178 aircraft leaving the major
airport in southern China, shipping about 25,000 passengers
traveling back home for the traditional Spring Festival falling on
Feb. 28 .
</P>
<P>
It is expected the highest daily air passengers departure can
reach as high as 30,000 people when passenger flow reaches its
peak in a few days.
</P>
<P>
To cope with the holiday crowds, the airport has recently added
50 more flights daily running on routes from Guangzhou, the
provincial capital of Guangdong, to major destinations such as
Chongqing, Guiyang, Chengdu, Yibin, Kunming, Haikou, Sanya,
Beijing, and Harbin.
</P>
<P>
