<HEADLINE> Overseas Chinese Affairs Departments Hold Reception </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 22 (Xinhua) -- At a reception today of
overseas Chinese affairs departments to celebrate the lunar new
year, Vice-Premier Qian Qichen said that overseas Chinese have
been a strong force in supporting China's development and have
contributed a lot to friendly relations with other countries.
</P>
<P>
They have also contributed to China's prosperity, Qian said,
and reviewed China's achievements during the past year, praising
overseas Chinese who have returned for their dedication to the
reforms and national development.
</P>
<P>
He said it is a common desire of all Chinese, both at home and
abroad, to achieve China's reunification. There need to be
economic and cultural exchanges across the Taiwan Straits under
the "peaceful reunification and one country, two systems" policy,
he said, so that there will be a smooth transition for Macao in
December of 1999.
</P>
<P>
He said he hopes that China's overseas Chinese affairs
departments will continue their efforts to increase ties with Hong
Kong, Macao, and Taiwan compatriots, and with overseas Chinese,
and work for new reform and opening-up developments this year.
</P>
<P>
Guo Dongpo, director of the State Council's Office of Overseas
Chinese Affairs, said that the sole purpose of overseas Chinese
affairs Departments is to serve overseas Chinese and that is their
responsibility as well. In the new year, they will do more
practical work for overseas Chinese and try to protect their
rights and interests.
</P>
<P>
The reception was organized by the Overseas Chinese Affairs
Committee of the National People's Congress, the Chinese People's
Political Consultative Conference's Liaison Subcommittee for
Taiwan, Hong Kong, and Macao Compatriots and Overseas Chinese, the
State Council's Office of Overseas Chinese Affairs, the China Zhi
Gong Party, and the All-China Federation of Returning Overseas
Chinese. 
