enthusiastic about donating money for education in China's
interior areas, an official with the State Education Commission
(SEC) said today.
</P>
<P>
"The Chinese nation has the fine tradition to respecting
teachers and value education, and many celebrities in Hong Kong do
not forget their motherland after they have succeeded in their
career," said Li Haiji, director of the Hong Kong, Macao and
Taiwan Affairs Office under the SEC.
</P>
<P>
With concerted efforts with the SEC, many well-known Hong Kong
figures, including Henry Fok Ying-tung and Tsang Hin-Chi, have
sponsored education foundations.
</P>
<P>
Since 1985, noted Hong Kong industrialist Run Run Shaw has
donated a total of 1.5 billion HK dollars to education causes in
China's interior areas.
</P>
<P>
In addition to contacting the SEC, many Hong Kong people made
direct donations to local governments or education institutions,
Li Haiji said, adding that many others chose to donate to the Hope
Project, a nationwide move to help kids from poor families.
</P>
<P>
After offering money, many donors went on discussing the use of
the money together with local education officials, so as to make
the money turn out the best benefits. 
