<HEADLINE> Rural Economy Grows in Fujian </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, January 22 (Xinhua) -- The rural economy in east
China's Fujian province enjoyed a 10 percent growth rate in
1997, with statistics showing that the province's rural output
value ended the year at 99.5 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
The province followed three consecutive years of good harvests
with a 1997 total grain output of 9.61 million tons.
</P>
<P>
Township enterprises recorded a total output value of 352
billion yuan, with the growth rate maintaining 20 percent.
</P>
<P>
The per capita income levels of the peasants rose by 10 percent
to 2,800 yuan.
</P>
<P>
The opening policy has promoted the development of the
export-oriented economy in rural areas, according to the local
government.
</P>
<P>
Fujian has established a group of bases to produce farm
products for export, with the product mix including aquatic
products, fruit and tea.
</P>
<P>
Rural areas have used foreign investments of two billion US
dollars to establish 3,200 foreign-funded firms.
</P>
<P>
The construction of disaster prevention projects, including a
flood warning system and coastal shelterbelts, have helped improve
the agricultural infrastructure and promoted the rural economy.
</P>
</TEXT>
