<HEADLINE> Tear Gas, Water Cannons Wait for Motorbike Racers in Hanoi </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, January 22 (Xinhua) -- Hanoi police have been authorized
to use tear gas and water cannons in their fight against illegal
motorbike racing, official press reported Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Illegal street racing has resurfaced over recent months and
police have voiced concern over a possible worsening during the
traditional Spring Festival holidays.
</P>
<P>
During the Christmas season, a major incident on December 24
left nine officers injured and four motorcycles destroyed by fire
after an angry mob attacked the police, the press said.
</P>
<P>
Following the incident, 51 youngsters were arrested and 181
charged with criminal acts.
</P>
<P>
In the run-up to the Tet (Spring Festival) which falls on
January 28, the report said, Hanoi police have intensified a
public awareness campaign and issued a warning that offenders will
be punished severely.
</P>
<P>
Police are also advising all shop and restaurant owners to
close by 11 p.m., the report said. 
</P>
