<HEADLINE> Vietnam to Bring Internal Strength Into Full Play </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, January 22 (Xinhua) -- Vietnam is determined to bring
internal resources and strength into full play, in the context of
the current financial and monetary crisis in Southeast Asia,
Vietnam's Communist Party chief Le Kha Phieu said.
</P>
<P>
Speaking to local officials during his recent tour of southern
provinces earlier this week, Phieu said that the Vietnamese people
should raise self-determination and self-reliance, and focus on
boosting production and economic development with priority given
to high-efficiency industries so as to make Vietnamese-made
products more competitive in the market, Vietnam News Agency
reported Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Vietnam should concentrate on export-oriented production and
avoid unplanned investment and waste of time, state assets and
funds, Phieu said.
</P>
<P>
He also stressed the need to practice thrift, saying that
"thrifty behavior in production and consumption must become a
national policy, responsibility and habit of all public agencies,
branches of activities, individual party cadres and members of
the entire people."
</P>
<P>
While meeting with foreign investors in Ho Chi Minh City, the
Vietnamese top leader said that Vietnam will continue to structure
and complete a legal environment that will enhance conditions for
foreign investors and business people in the country.
</P>
<P>
Phieu reassured that his country will maintain multi-sector
economy and an open-door policy. 
</P>
</TEXT>
