<HEADLINE> Philippine President Vows to Ensure Peaceful Transfer </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, January 22 (Xinhua) -- Philippine President Fidel Ramos
Thursday renewed his assurance of a peaceful transfer of power
this year and urged foreign investors not to be distracted by the
May 11 elections.
</P>
<P>
In a speech delivered to both local and foreign investors,
Ramos said the peaceful turnover of power is "a normal and regular
happening" in the Philippines.
</P>
<P>
He said whoever succeeds him after June 30 is believed to be
able to sustain the continuity of the basic policies governing the
economy.
</P>
<P>
That was because "there is a degree of policy consensus among
the parties and the candidates on the economy," Ramos said, adding
that all the presidential hopefuls "subscribe to a free market
economy" and acknowledge the country's need for competitiveness in
the world.
</P>
<P>
He urged foreign investors not to be "distracted by the
sometimes inflated rhetoric, political noises and circus
atmosphere" that attend the Philippine electoral contests.
</P>
<P>
Analysts said honest and orderly elections and a peaceful
transfer of power would help the Philippines overcome the current
currency crisis. 
</P>
