<DATE_TIME> 1998-01-22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Shanghai Company Enlivens Real Estate Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, January 22 (Xinhua) -- A new Shanghai real estate
company is offering purchase, lease and auction services.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai Dekang Housing Property Purchase and Lease Co. Ltd.,
the first company of its kind in China's largest metropolis, is
expected to enliven the fiercely competitive local property
market, according to Chairman Zhou Fuheng.
</P>
<P>
Policies enable the company to either purchase property from
developers outright, find tenants for a vacant properties, or
sell when the market takes a turn for the better.
</P>
<P>
The company offers a "zero risk, high return" package to find
tenants for property owners. Owners can also mortgage property or
ask the company to auction the property on their behalf.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai Dekang will also assist banks in purchase and mortgage
transactions. 
</P>
</TEXT>
