<DATE_TIME> 1998-01-22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Guangdong Workers Live Better </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, January 22 (Xinhua) -- Workers in Guangzhou, capital
of south China's Guangdong province, steadily improved their
living standard in the previous year.
</P>
<P>
Experts owes such improvement to the growth of workers' actual
income and the expansion of social security system in Guangzhou,
which is working hard to ensure workers' basic living conditions.
</P>
<P>
Latest statistics show that the workers' total salary volume
from January to November in 1997 reached 20.5 billion yuan (about
2.5 billion U.S.dollars), or 1,144 yuan per capita, up by 11.8
percent and 14.4 percent respectively over the same period of 1996.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, workers, particularly the 350,000 retired ones,
benefit much from a diversity of insurances of old age, industrial
injury and unemployment.
</P>
<P>
The city also increased the relief fund from 210 yuan to 250
yuan for those workers whose monthly family income is lower than
240 yuan each.  
</P>
</TEXT>
