<HEADLINE> Shanghai Gets New Robotics Manufacturing Plant </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, January 22 (Xinhua) -- Shanghai and Japanese firms
have recently formed a robotics manufacturing company in Shanghai,
China's largest industrial center.
</P>
<P>
The Shanghai Fanuc Robotics Co. Ltd. is the first company of
its kind in Shanghai.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai Electronics Corporation and Japanese-based Fanuc
Co. Ltd founded the company with a total investment of 1.4 million
US dollars. The venture will market robotic products and offer
post-sales services for the machine-building and automobile
manufacturing industries. It will also help the industrial sectors
train specialists and will design automated production lines.
</P>
<P>
