<HEADLINE> China Issues 241 Billion Yuan in Treasury Bonds in 1997 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 22 (Xinhua) -- China reached its treasury
bond issue targets for 1997, with government bonds valued at over
241.2 billion yuan (29.13 billion US dollars) issued by the end
of the year, according to the Ministry of Finance.
</P>
<P>
The redemption of treasury bonds due last year has basically
been completed, according to the ministry.
</P>
<P>
Major improvements were made in last year's treasury bond issue
procedures in order to meet the needs of individual investors,
with individuals purchasing over 85 percent of the total issue.
</P>
<P>
Supervision of the bond market has also been reinforced, with
clear progress achieved in infrastructure, market order and
mechanisms to avoid trade risks.
</P>
<P>
The Ministry noted this year's treasury bond issue will remain
oriented towards individuals, and the bond market will be further
directed towards healthy, stable and regulated development.
</P>
</TEXT>
