<HEADLINE> China Absorbs Overseas Funds in Mining Industry </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 22 (Xinhua) -- China's mining industry drew
11.44 million US dollars of foreign funds in 1997, double the
total used in the years before.
</P>
<P>
The funds were used to tap over 20 types of mineral including
gold and diamond, according to sources from the Ministry of
Geology and Mineral Resources.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the country also made efforts to develop
international market. So far, 13 Chinese provinces and
municipalities have launched projects of mineral exploration in 13
countries, which involve such minerals as gold, diamond and
sylvite.
</P>
<P>
Song Ruixiang, minister of Geology and Mineral Resources, said
that China will further strengthen its cooperation with other
countries in the mining industry and focus on such minerals as
iron, copper, manganese, chromium, cobalt, gold and sylvite.
