<HEADLINE> Traffic Accidents Kill Over 5,300 in Poland in 1997 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WARSAW, January 21 (Xinhua) -- As many as 5,323 people were
killed in 66,769 traffic accidents in Poland in 1997, 16.1 percent
up from the previous year, Poland's newspaper Rzeczypospolita
reported Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Another 85,136 people were wounded in these accidents which
went up by 15.3 percent from 1996, the paper added.
</P>
<P>
The paper said one of the reasons for the increasing traffic
accidents was the gap between the poor road condition and the ever
more vehicles. An average of 500,000 vehicles are annually
registered in Poland.
</P>
<P>
However, the paper held speeding as the main reason for the
situation. It said some 40 percent of the dead lost their lives in
the speed-related accidents. 
</P>
