<HEADLINE> Ningxia to Expand Private Sector </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YINCHUAN, January 22 (Xinhua) -- Northwest China's Ningxia Hui
Autonomous Region plans to increase the proportion of its private
sector contributions to GDP by five percent annually over the next
five years.
</P>
<P>
"Regional economic growth relies to a great extent on the
healthy progress of the private sector," according to Ma Qizhi,
acting chairman of the regional government.
</P>
<P>
The region's state sector accounts for 70 percent of the
local economy, some 20 percentage points higher than the
national average. However, the majority of related
enterprises are operating at a loss.
</P>
<P>
"We will treat the private sector as the state-owned
economy, and breathe new vitality into the hard-pressed state-run
sector by allowing the former to merge with the latter," according
to Mao Rubai, a senior official of the regional government.
</P>
<P>
Related departments are formulating additional favorable
policies to protect the interests of the private sector.  
</P>
