<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's Cement Industry Predicts Moderate Growth </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 22 (Xinhua) -- China is expected to produce
530 million tons of cement this year, up about four percent from
last year, according to official projections.
</P>
<P>
The country is expected to have a better macro-economic
environment, with economic growth expected to be above eight
percent.
</P>
<P>
China intends to push the average living space to about nine
sq.m. for each urban resident by the year 2000, which means 240
million sq.m. of residential housing will be built annually over
the next three years, giving a boost to the cement industry.
</P>
<P>
Other factors to contribute to the industry's growth include
increased spending on water conservation, continuing large state
construction projects like the Three Gorges Dam, and highway,
railway, and urban infrastructure construction.
</P>
<P>
Continued reforms in the industry will have a positive impact
on the cement market. China now has over 8,000 cement producers,
only 500 of which have a production capacity of more than 200,000
tons and many of the older and smaller factories are expected to
be restructured this year.  
</P>
</TEXT>
