<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Developing Marine Economy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAIKOU, January 22 (Xinhua) -- China has achieved an average
annual increase of 20 percent for its marine economy for the past
few years, according to a recent ocean development conference.
</P>
<P>
China has been moving to improve its marine industry structure,
which is dominated by fishery and marine plantations. And, as
offshore oil has come to account for an ever greater part of the
world's marine economy, China, which is said to have 18 percent of
the world's offshore oil resources, is only producing two percent
of the world's annual offshore oil output.
</P>
<P>
China also lags behind in extracting magnesium, potassium, and
bromine from sea water, as well as in sea water desalination,
pharmaceuticals from the sea, and oceanographic electronics. So it
is attempting to have more rapid development in these areas.
</P>
<P>
The country has 18,000 km of coastline, and ocean industries
will be significant to the development of energy, the chemical
industry, foodstuff, and medicine, experts say. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980122.0188 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-01-22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Premier Meets With Russian Defense Secretary </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 22 (Xinhua) -- Premier Li Peng, meeting this
morning with Andrei Kokoshin, chief military inspector and
secretary of Russia's Defense Council, said that Sino-Russian
friendly cooperation has been fruitful with the five meetings
between President Jiang Zemin and President Boris Yeltsin and
other efforts of the past several years.
</P>
<P>
The two countries have decided to establish a 21st-century
strategic partnership of cooperation based on equality and mutual
trust, and will keep to the principle of mutual respect,
good-neighborly friendship, reciprocal cooperation, seeking common
development, non-alignment, non-confrontation, and not appealing
to a third party, Li said.
</P>
<P>
This complies with the fundamental interests of the people of
the two countries and conducive to regional and world peace and
stability, he went on to say, noting that, in 1997, there were a
number of major events and it was an unusual year in China, but
that this year is also important for the overall implementation of
the various tasks of the 15th Party Congress.
</P>
<P>
The country will continue the principle of seeking progress in
steady development and pushing various reforms, opening-up, and
economic development, Li added.
</P>
<P>
He voiced support for exchanges between the military and public
security departments and said he is convinced that Kokoshin's
visit will help develop the friendly cooperation between
departments.
</P>
<P>
Kokoshin said that the Russian government values the continued
development of bilateral friendship and cooperation, and that
there is great potential for bilateral cooperation.
</P>
<P>
The Vice-Chairman of China's Central Military Commission and
Defense Minister Chi Haotian, and Russian Ambassador to China Igor
A. Rogachev were present at the meeting.
</P>
<P>
Kokoshin arrived here this morning for a six-day official
goodwill visit to China as Chi's guest. 
</P>
</TEXT>
