<HEADLINE> US Industrial Gas Producer Invests in Chinese City </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGSHA, January 22 (Xinhua) -- Praxair, a major US industrial
gas producer, has signed a contract on the construction of a
carbon dioxide recycling facility in Yueyang, central China's
Hunan Province.
</P>
<P>
The multinational industrial gas supplier will invest eight
million US dollars in first phase construction. The plant, which
will have an annual production capacity of 30,000 tons, will be the
largest foreign-funded project in Yueyang.
</P>
<P>
The facility will, by using state-of-the-art equipment,
transform industrial waste gas emitted by the Baling Yingshan
Petrochemical Plant into solid carbon dioxide.  
