<HEADLINE> Hunan's Provincial Capital Strengthens Environmental Protection </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGSHA, January 22 (Xinhua) -- Changsha, capital of central
China's Hunan Province, plans to allocate 11.3 million yuan (1.4
million US dollars) to launch 10 environmental protection projects.
</P>
<P>
The projects involve dust emissions, noise pollution, and waste
water treatment, according an official with the city's
environmental protection bureau.
</P>
<P>
On-site supervision of key sources of pollution has been
strengthened to ensure effective treatment, with more than 90
percent of treatment facilities operating smoothly.
</P>
<P>
Some 60 sources of noise pollution and 95 enterprises creating
other types of pollutants have been closed, and the environmental
protection bureau have effectively resolved over 95 percent of
complaints filed by local residents.  
</P>
