<DOCNO> XIE19980122.0200 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-01-22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> El Nino May not Affect Whole Zambia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, January 22 (xinhua) -- El Nino may not affect whole
Zambia apart from the extremes of southern, western and north
western provinces, a local meteorologist said here Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The Post today quoted meteorologist Richard Mugara as saying
that so far Zambia has received normal rainfall apart from the
areas mentioned above.
</P>
<P>
He told the national Program to Prevent Malnutrition (PPM)
meeting that "effects of El Nino on Zambia result in dryer than
normal condition."
</P>
<P>
In a paper presented to the meeting he said if El Nino reaches
its maximum intensity this month then it will take four weeks to
start experiencing dry spells and that will be end of February,
meaning that those who planted their seeds early may service the
drought whilest those who planted late will be badly affected.
</P>
<P>
But if El Nino reaches its maximum intensity in February then
Zambia will start experiencing dry spells in March meaning that
crops will not be affected as that is actually the end of the
rain season, Mugara said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
