<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 0800 GMT, January 22 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIRANA -- A police unrest in Shkodra, a large town in northern
Albania, cooled down on Wednesday afternoon, Albanian news media
reported.
</P>
<P>
The armed rebel policemen, who captured the Shkodra government
building for more than a day, withdrew at 4:50 p.m. local time and
the tension tended to calm.
</P>
<P>
Key organs of the town and major state highways were under
control of the local police and the commandos coming from
Tirana. (Albania-Police Unrest)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
MOSCOW -- Russian Prime Minister Viktor Chernomyrdin Wednesday
met visiting Belarussian President Alexandr Lukashenko on
prospects of furthering bilateral economic and political
cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Chernomyrdin, Lukashenko and Belarussian Prime Minister Segei
Ling also exchanged views on preparations for the meeting of the
Supreme Committee of the Russia-Belarus Union scheduled for
Thursday, said the Itar-Tass news agency. Trade volume between
Russia and Belarussia in 1997 increased 40 percent over the
previous year as a result of their close economic cooperation.
(Russia-Belarus)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
TOKYO -- Japan's merchandise trade surplus in 1997 jumped up by
48.5 percent from the previous year to 10,008.3 billion yen (about
78.5 billion U.S. dollars), marking the first yearly increase
since 1992, the Finance Ministry said Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The ministry attributed the increase to robust exports of
automobiles and the depreciation of the yen against the
U.S. dollar. Japan's exports went up by 13.9 percent to 50,948.2
billion yen (about 400 billion dollars), while imports increased
by 7.8 percent to 40,939.9 billion yen (about 321.2 billion
dollars) in 1997, the ministry said in a preliminary
report. (Japan-Trade Surplus)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
TIRANA -- Italian Prime Minister Romanno Prodi Wednesday
arrived in Skopje, capital of Macedonia, for a one-day visit to
boost bilateral ties.
</P>
<P>
In a meeting with Macedonian leaders, Prodi, the first Italian
prime minister to visit Macedonia since it proclaimed its
independence from Yugoslavia in 1991, appreciated Macedonia's role
in maintaining peace and stability in the Balkan region.
(Macedonia-Italy) 
</P>
</TEXT>
