<HEADLINE> China Computerizes Coal Industry </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, January 22 (Xinhua) -- Efficiency in China's coal
mines has increased a great deal thanks to the application of
information technology over the past decade.
</P>
<P>
More than 90 key state-owned mines are using computers to help
figure production, management, sales, accounting, supplies, and
salaries.
</P>
<P>
A special telecommunications network for the industry with a
5,000-km digital microwave trunk line, a 1,500-km optical fiber
cable, 82 satellite ground receiving stations, and four provincial
microwave networks is helping in all this.
</P>
<P>
All large state-owned coal dressing plants and production
mineshafts are being regulated with monitoring systems.
</P>
<P>
The administrations of Shandong, Shanxi, and Sichuan provinces
have compatible computer systems at their offices, and the amount
of time involved in coal transport has been shortened and
production costs reduced. 
</P>
