<HEADLINE> Namibia, Botswana Islands Dispute Briefed to </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, January 22 (xinhua) -- Namibian President Sam Nujoma
paid a brief call to his Zimbabwean counterpart Robert Mugabe in
Harare to acquaint him on the progress in negotiations on the
dispute between his country and Botswana over islands on their
common border.
</P>
<P>
After his arrival Wednesday, the two leaders went into a
closed meeting for over one hour in which he briefed Mugabe, in
his capacity as chairman of the organ on security and conflict
resolution in the Southern African Development Community (SADC)
region, on the latest developments to the conflict.
</P>
<P>
