light of the recent political developments within the SADC.
</P>
<P>
Namibia and Botswana have been locked in a dispute over the
Situngu Islands in the Caprivi region on the Linyanti river. This
is already being looked into by the two countries' joint
commission on defence and security which has already met on
several occasions to try and find a solution to the problem.
</P>
<P>
The dispute over the smaller island on the Chobe river is
being adjudicated by the world court in the Hague of the
Netherlands.
</P>
<P>
In mid-January, there were reports that Botswana defense
forces had occupied two Situngu islands and had harassed Namibian
farmers for having planted their crops there.  
