<HEADLINE> Shenzhen and Hongkong Enhance Cooperation in Financial Sector </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENZHEN, January 22 (Xinhua) -- Financial institutions in the
Shenzhen Special Economic Zone and the Hong Kong Special
Administrative Region (HKSAR) expanded cooperation during 1997.
</P>
<P>
The linking of ATM (automatic teller machines) and POS (point
of sales) networks in the neighboring areas during 1997 provided
greater convenience for trans-regional financial settlements.
</P>
<P>
Five Shenzhen banks provided loans, accepted deposits and
handle settlements for Hong Kong enterprises during the year. The
so-called "offshore financial business" provided by local and
overseas financial institutions in Shenzhen ended the year with
deposits totalling 2.79 billion US dollars and loans of 2.44
billion US dollars.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong financial institutions have opened 10 facilities and
12 representative offices in Shenzhen.
</P>
<P>
Three leading Shenzhen companies raised a total of 4.8 billion
yuan from listings on the Hong Kong Stock Exchange, with related
funds mainly earmarked for development projects in the city.
</P>
<P>
Related financial institutions jointly organized seminars to
exchange views on wide-ranging topics, including regulating and
using financial derivatives, risk management and life insurance.
 
</P>
