<HEADLINE> Tianjin Bonded Zone Fulfills Economic Targets </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, January 22 (Xinhua) -- The Tianjin Bonded Zone
outdistanced all other bonded zones in China in terms of 1997
economic growth.
</P>
<P>
The zone signed contracts valued at 850 million U.S. dollars
during 1997, up 72 percent on the previous year. The value of
foreign-related contracts grew by 75 percent to 700 million
U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
The total value of goods foreign trade departments purchased
for import and export grew dramatically by 83 percent to end the
year at four billion U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
The actual import-export volume climbed to a record one billion
U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
The zone has established relatively complete infrastructure,
trade and customs systems over the past five years, and has
attracted investors from 73 countries and regions, including
US-based Caltex and Caterpillar, Itochu of Japan and Daewoo from
the Republic of Korea.
</P>
<P>
A large number of medium- to large-sized state-owned
enterprises have established operations in the zone, with
investment totalling 200 million U.S. dollars.  
</P>
