<HEADLINE> Hunan Electronics Sector Turns Losses into Profits </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGSHA, January 22 (Xinhua) -- The electronics sector in
central-south China's Hunan Province earned profits of three
million yuan (361.440 US dollars) in 1997, thereby ending losses
recorded since 1991.
</P>
<P>
The industry witnessed substantial growth in output value for
1996, but nonetheless recorded heavy losses of over 100 million
yuan (12 million US dollars).
</P>
<P>
The sector generated a gross 1997 output value of 3.4
billion yuan, a year-on-year rise of 65 percent.
</P>
<P>
Provincial officials attributed the progress to successful
efforts to restructure enterprises in the sector.
</P>
<P>
Some 75 percent of Hunan's electronics enterprises have an
annual output values of less than 10 million yuan each, a level
which severely restricts competitiveness. The province established
a large electronics conglomerate -- Hunan Electronic Information
Industrial Group-- in 1996 as part of an effort to overcome the
problem.
</P>
<P>
In addition, the LG-Shuguang Color Television Tube Co., a joint
venture set up with investments from the Republic of Korea (ROK),
completed first phase construction in May 1997 and substantially
increased the mass production capacity.  
</P>
</TEXT>
