<HEADLINE> Guangdong Banking Sector Remains Sound </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, January 22 (Xinhua) -- The banking sector in
Guangdong Province, one of China's economic powerhouses, developed
along a healthy track in 1997, with all indicators pointing to a
continuing surge upwards.
</P>
<P>
Statistics released during a recent provincial financial work
meeting show that bank deposits hit 92.66 billion yuan (11.16
billion US dollars), a year-on-year rise of 16.44 billion yuan,
with loans outstanding rising by 8.57 billion yuan to end the year
at 69.98 billion yuan. Savings deposits topped 56.13 billion yuan,
up 9.99 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
The importance of Guangdong's financial sector is fully
illustrated by the fact that outstanding and new deposits, as well
as deposits by enterprises and residents account for some 10
percent of the national total.  
