<HEADLINE> Albania, Russia to Sign Friendship Treaty </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIRANA, January 21 (Xinhua) -- Albanian President Rexhep
Mejdani said Wednesday he accepted Russian President Boris
Yeltsin's invitation to visit Moscow and sign a friendship and
cooperation treaty.
</P>
<P>
The invitation was contained in a letter delivered Wednesday
through Russia's ambassador to Albania, reported the Albanian news
agency ATA.
</P>
<P>
In his meeting with the Russian ambassador, Mejdani said he
agreed with Yeltsin that his Moscow tour would be important for
cementing a partnership between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
It would also help strengthen stability in the region, he said.
</P>
<P>
As media reports went, Yeltsin also pledged support in the
letter for stability and democracy in Albania, saying that Russia
would deepen cooperation with the Balkan nation.
</P>
<P>
The ATA report did not give a specific date for the proposed
Moscow trip by the Albanian president. 
</P>
</TEXT>
