<DATE_TIME> 1998-01-22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Japan's Trade Surplus Up 48.5 Percent in 1997 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, January 22 (Xinhua) -- Japan's merchandise trade surplus
in 1997 jumped up 48.5 percent from the previous year to 10,008.3
billion yen, marking the first yearly increase since 1992, the
Finance Ministry said Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The ministry attributed the increase to robust exports of
automobiles and the depreciation of the yen against the
U.S. dollar.
</P>
<P>
Japan's exports went up 13.9 percent to 50,948.2 billion yen,
while imports increased 7.8 percent to 40,939.9 billion yen in
1997, the ministry said in a preliminary report.
</P>
<P>
Japan's politically sensitive trade surplus with the United
States in the year surged 41.7 percent to 5,024.5 billion yen, the
ministry said. Japan's trade surplus in December jumped 40.9
percent from a year earlier to 1,238.2 billion yen, marking the
ninth straight month of year-on-year increase.
</P>
<P>
Japan's trade surplus with the European Union and Asia in the
reporting year also turned upward. The surplus with the EU rose
67.3 percent to 2,482 billion yen, the first expansion in five
years and that with Asian countries went up 14.4 percent to 6,359
billion yen for the first rise in two years.
</P>
<P>
A ministry official said that Japan's trade surplus will
continue to rise in the short term but that it is not expected to
sharply expand from the medium to long term. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980122.0227 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-01-22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Nepal Acts to Relieve Shortage of Fertilizers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, January 22 (Xinhua) -- The Nepali government has
formulated new policies aimed at relieving the acute shortage of
fertilizers throughout the country by involving the private sector
in importing fertilizers, national newspapers reported Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Under the policies, private sector companies and firms are not
required to seek licenses for importing urea and other chemical
fertilizers.
</P>
<P>
The foreign exchange needed will be made available through
simplified procedures, the imported fertilizers can be forwarded
to any part of the country without hindrance and the importers
themselves can set the retail prices, the newspapers said.
</P>
<P>
These measures are expected to make prices in the chemical
fertilizer market competitive and make quality fertilizers
available to farmers on time and at reasonable prices, the
newspapers said.
</P>
<P>
The Himalayan kingdom, which defends heavily on agriculture, is
facing a severe shortage of fertilizers.
</P>
<P>
The state-run Agricultural Inputs Corporation had monopolized
the fertilizer market in the country, leading to rampant smuggling
of fertilizers across the open border with India.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
