<HEADLINE> Myanmar Farmers Urged to Boost Paddy Output </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, January 22 (Xinhua) -- Myanmar leader Khin Nyunt urged
farmers in the country to cultivate more summer paddy to boost the
yield.
</P>
<P>
Khin Nyunt, first secretary of the Myanmar State Peace and
Development Council, made the call Tuesday when he inspected an
agricultural station in Myaungmya, Ayeyawaddy division, the
official newspaper The New Light of Myanmar reported Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The division has been traditionally producing about one third
of the total paddy output in the country.
</P>
<P>
A total of 6.48 million hectares is being targeted to be under
paddy in the whole country including 4.86 million hectares of
monsoon paddy and 1.62 million hectares of summer paddy.
</P>
<P>
Myanmar set the output target of 20 million tons of paddy for
the 1997-98 fiscal year, the second year of its present five-year
plan (1996-97 to 2000-01).  
</P>
</TEXT>
