<HEADLINE> Hingis Leaps Up Later into Third Round </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, January 22 (Xinhua) -- World number one Martina
Hingis overcame a first-set scar to breeze pass German Barbara
Rittner, 7-5, 6-1, to move into the third round of the Australian
Open on Thursday in Melbourne, Australia.
</P>
<P>
The Swiss sensitional squandered a 5-0 lead in the opening
set, letting her 73rd-ranked rival breaking twice to tie at 5-5.
</P>
<P>
Suffering the first-serve errors through the match, Hingis
held onto her domination in the second when Rittner broke at the
third game.
</P>
<P>
Hingis cooled herself with a cup of water before the reigning
champion stepped into the court and pulled away for good. 
</P>
