<HEADLINE> Peruvian Exports Up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LIMA, January 21 (Xinhua) -- Peru's exports totalled 6.2
billion U.S. dollars in January-November 1997, a 16 percent
increase over the same period last year, the national Central
Reserve Bank said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Of the 850 million dollar increase in exports, 433 million
dollars were traditional agricultural and fishery products, and
417 million dollars non-traditional textile and steel products,
the bank said.
</P>
<P>
Imports, on the other hand, reached 7.8 billion dollars in the
first 11 months of 1997, resulting in a trade deficit of 1.6
billion dollars. 
</P>
