<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Lee Kuan Yew Urges Thai Political Continuity </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, January 22 (Xinhua) -- Singapore's Senior Minister Lee
Kuan Yew has urged political continuity in Thailand so as to boost
international confidence in the country's ability to recover from
the economic slump.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a National Defense College seminar on Wednesday in
Bangkok, Lee also called on the United States and Japan to help
tackle the crisis in East Asia before it harms world trade and
regional security, the Bangkok Post reported on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Thailand needs to assure foreign companies and investors that
the next election would bring a competent government, Lee said.
</P>
<P>
If they perceive that the next government has the same weakness
as past administrations, confidence will remain weak, he added.
</P>
<P>
Lee noted that in the past five years, Thailand has changed
government several times and none stayed long enough in office to
deal with the growing current account deficits and increasing US
dollar debt which was going into property developments.
</P>
<P>
He said the United States should include Thailand and Indonesia
in its bid to help ensure stability in Southeast Asia, adding the
economic slump in the region would hurt American exporters and
slow US economic growth.
</P>
<P>
"The cost to the United States of not doing anything in Asia
will be high. The United States must, in its own economic
interest, extend its help beyond South Korea to include Thailand
and Indonesia," he urged.
</P>
<P>
Concerning Japan, Lee said a strong Japanese economy was crucial
because it would encourage Japanese consumers to spend more money
buying Asian products.
</P>
<P>
"Japan must quickly get its economic back into health. A strong
Japanese economy will help our recovery by boosting our exports, "
lee said.
</P>
<P>
Lee expressed confidence that Asian countries in economic
difficulties will recover within two or three years if there is no
external problem.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
