<HEADLINE> Michael Klim Sets 100m Butterfly World Record </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, January 22 (Xinhua) -- Australia's Michael Klim set a
short course world record for the 100 meters butterfly at a World
Cup swimming meet on Thursday in Sydney, Australia.
</P>
<P>
Klim's new world record is 51.16 seconds, 0.62 seconds better
than the previous mark set by Russia's Denis Pankratov last year
in Paris, France. 
</P>
</TEXT>
