<HEADLINE> IDB Launches First Greek Drachma Bond Issue </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, January 21 (Xinhua) -- The Inter-American
Development Bank (IDB) today announced the launching of its first
Greek Drachma bond issue for GRD10 billion which is about 34.5
million U.S. dollars equivalent under the Euro Medium-Term Note
Program.
</P>
<P>
The issue was priced at 101 percent, pays a 12 percent annual
coupon, and matures on February 2, 2000.
</P>
<P>
Morgan Stanley is the lead manager of a syndicate of
international banks placing the issue.
</P>
<P>
The proceeds of the issue are swapped into U.S. dollars and
will be incorporated into the IDB's ordinary capital and used to
finance the economic and social development projects in Latin
America and the Caribbean. 
