<HEADLINE> East African Leaders to Meet on Further </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ARUSHA (Tanzania), January 21 (Xinhua) -- Presidents of Kenya,
Tanzania and Uganda are scheduled to open a summit here on April
28 in a bid to integrate the East African Cooperation (EAC) into
a single market and a political confederation.
</P>
<P>
As part of preparation, a three-day meeting of the EAC High
Level Tripartite Committee started today with a special focus on
how to remove the impediments to the promotion of inter-state
trade, EAC Secretary-General Francis Muthaura told Xinhua in an
exclusive interview.
</P>
<P>
"A draft (of an upgraded EAC Treaty) should be ready in the
next one or two months" and be discussed at the coming summit, he
said.
</P>
<P>
The EAC is planning to realize " zero tariff" within itself by
2000 while listing a single currency the first target afterwards,
he said.
</P>
<P>
Currently, the three EAC states have narrowed taxation
differences and share the same tariff preference policies
available in COMESA.
</P>
<P>
The three east African countries "are also developing a joint
investment and export promotion strategy" so as to harmonize
their policies to attract more foreign investments, he said,
adding the strategy is expected to be high on the agenda of the
coming summit.
</P>
<P>
Among priorities of further economic integrity are also the
setting-up of a digital transmission network, a database system
and a joint stock exchange, as well as closer cooperation in the
fields of tourism, energy, science research and infrastructure
improvement, according to Muthaura.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the EAC is planning a long-term road construction
program under which as long as 12,805 kilometers of road, at a
cost of some 4.67 billion U.S Dollars, will be built within the
region, he said.
</P>
<P>
He also called for more Chinese investment in the region as
China has been playing a more and more active role in the
regional economy over recent years. The region's imports from
China are increasing sharply, he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
