<HEADLINE> UNITA Weapons Found in Angola </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, January 21 (Xinhua) -- Police in Angola have
discovered more than 1,000 weapons and ammunition hidden in
caches by Angola's former rebel UNITA movement, local press
reported today.
</P>
<P>
Police said the arms were found at Milunga in the northern
Uije province. The stockpiles were created for militiamen of the
National Union for the Total Independence of Angola (UNITA), who
recently handed Milunga back to government forces in line with a
1994 peace pact.
