<HEADLINE> Iranian FM Calls for Ending Algerian Massacres </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, January 21 (Xinhua) -- Iranian Foreign Minister Kamal
Kharrazi Wednesday called on two regional organizations to use
their influences to end the ongoing massacres in Algeria.
</P>
<P>
According to the Iranian official news agency IRNA, Kharrazi
sent two separate letters to Secretary General of the Arab League
Esmat Abdel-Meguid and Secretary General of the Organization of
African Unity (OAU) Salem Ahmad Salem, voicing his concern about
the continuing massacres of civilians in Algeria.
</P>
<P>
In his letters, Kharrazi said that massacres of civilians in
Algeria had caused deep regret and concern in Arab, Islamic and
African nations, prompting every responsible government to offer
every possible assistance for an immediate halt to the unprovoked
killings in that country.
</P>
<P>
He said that the cooperation of regional organizations would
obviously help end the massacres in Algeria.
</P>
<P>
Kharrazi said that Iran, as chairman of the Organization of the
Islamic Conference (OIC) is ready and willing to offer every
possible assistance for curbing bloodshed in Algeria.
</P>
<P>
Following the massacre of over 400 people in Algeria in recent
weeks, Kharrazi has contacted with foreign ministers of Italy,
Syria, Morocco, Greece and France and sent letters to heads of
several international organizations including U.N Secretary
General Kofi Annan, calling for international efforts to put an
end to the Algerian tragedy. 
</P>
