<HEADLINE> AL Denounces US for Arming Israel With F-15Is </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, January 21 (Xinhua) -- The Arab League (AL) Wednesday
criticized Washington for providing Israel with advanced F-15I war
jets as baring its bias towards the Jewish state.
</P>
<P>
"The U.S. move is contradicting the principle of neutrality the
U.S. ought to adhere to as a main sponsor of the Mideast peace
process," said AL Assistant Secretary General Ahmed bin Holei.
</P>
<P>
Quoted by Egypt's Middle East News Agency, Holei voiced regret
over the step to beef up the Israeli air force when Washington is
renewing its mediation efforts to end the 10-month-old deadlock in
the Palestinian-Israeli peace talks.
</P>
<P>
In what many see as a make-or-break attempt to save the peace
process, U.S. President Bill Clinton held talks with Israeli Prime
Minister Benjamin Netanyahu in the White House Tuesday and will
meet with Palestinian National Authority President Yasser Arafat
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Beating a pessimistic note, the Arab League official said
nothing more can be expected from the Washington meetings.
</P>
<P>
"The general mood is that the meetings are expected to fail in
view of the Israeli Likud government's insistence on closing all
doors to advancing the stalled Mideast peace drive," he said.
</P>
<P>
The negotiations on the Palestinian track hit a deadlock after
Israel began to build a new settlement in Arab East Jerusalem
last March and a spate of suicide bombings followed.
</P>
<P>
Israel has purchased 25 U.S.-made F-15I war planes. The arrival
of the first two of them in Israel Monday has prompted fear among
the Arab states.
</P>
<P>
The F-15I planes, with a range of at least 4,500 kilometers, are
among the fastest warplanes in the world. It can fly at double the
speed of sound carrying 11 tonnes of missiles and bombs. They
enable Israel to strike targets as far as Iraq, Iran and Libya
without refueling.
</P>
<P>
Israel now possesses 90 F-15 planes, 112 Phantoms (F-4), 160
F-16 Falcons and 94 Israeli Kafir planes, and are seeking more,
according to local strategic experts.
</P>
<P>
In addition to a reconnaissance squadron of 24 Phantoms and
four early warning planes, Israel has two tanker planes to refuel
planes in the air and 22 Hercules transport planes. There are also
96 Skyhawks in store. 
</P>
</TEXT>
