<HEADLINE> World Bank Assists Gaza Industrial Estate Project </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, January 21 (Xinhua) -- The World Bank today
announced the approval of a 10 million U.S. dollar credit to
assist the Palestinians in establishing its first export-oriented
industrial zone in the West Bank and Gaza.
</P>
<P>
The Gaza Industrial Estate Project will provide financing for
off-site infrastructure, with the aim of creating up to 50,000
jobs in the Gaza Strip.
</P>
<P>
With a total cost of 84.5 million dollars, the project will
help create a more secure and predictable environment for private
sector investment, including building the necessary physical
infrastructure for industrial activity.
</P>
<P>
Some 20,000 permanent direct jobs are to be created at the Gaza
Industrial Estate and nearly 30,000 indirect jobs in the Gaza
Strip.
</P>
<P>
The World Bank's 10 million dollar credit is from the Trust
Fund for Gaza and West Bank on the terms of the International
Development Association (IDA), the concessionary lending wing of
the World Bank for developing countries. The European Investment
Bank (EIB) is providing 5 million dollars equivalent in equity and
the United States Agency for International Development (USAID)
will provide 6.3 million dollars for off-site infrastructure,
technical assistance and training. The Palestinian Authority has
provided land for the site with a lease value of 23.5 million
dollars. 
</P>
</TEXT>
