<HEADLINE> 183 Kilograms of Heroin Seized in Turkey </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, January 21 (Xinhua) -- A total of 183 kilograms of
heroin has been seized in an operation against drug trafficking in
Turkey's largest city of Istanbul, an official statement said
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The semi-official Anatolia News Agency quoted the statement
issued by Turkey's Gendarme Commandership as saying that acting
on a tip-off, Gendarme soldiers searched Gocbeyli village in Tuzla
town of Istanbul and found the heroin in the area. However, it did
not say when the heroin was confiscated.
</P>
<P>
It said that four suspects were detained in connection with
drug smuggling.
</P>
<P>
Turkey is a key transit route of drugs to Europe from the area
bordering Afghanistan and Pakistan. In 1996, Turkish police seized
4.4 tonnes of heroin, or 40 percent of the world's total
haul. 
</P>
