<HEADLINE> Turkey Probes Assets of Banned Welfare Party </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, January 21 (Xinhua) -- Turkish authorities are
investigating the assets of the recently banned pro-Islamic
Welfare Party (RP) both at home and abroad, semi-official Anatolia
News Agency reported Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Finance Ministry officials began procedures just after the
decision to authorize the ministry to investigate the RP's assets
was officially published Monday, according to the news agency.
</P>
<P>
The ministry had already completed the groundwork on the probe
into RP's assets since the decision to shut down the party was
announced last Friday by the Constitutional Court, said the news
agency.
</P>
<P>
It added that the investigation will also involve cooperation
with the interior and justice ministries.
</P>
<P>
Provincial administrations all over the country will set up
commissions to confiscate all inventories of the local RP offices,
the report said.
</P>
<P>
If any evidence of possible RP's overseas assests is
discovered, the commission will send inspectors to the concerned
countries to carry out a probe.
</P>
<P>
The RP was closed on charges of its violation of the secular
principles of the country. 
</P>
