<HEADLINE> Turkey to Buy 26 Boeings </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, January 21 (Xinhua) -- The Turkish Airlines (THY)
signed a credit agreement with U.S. Eximbank and Boeing company
Wednesday to buy 26 Boeing 737-800 aircraft, semi-official
Anatolia News Agency reported Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Under the 2.5 billion-dollar agreement, the 85 percent of the
deal will be met by loans of the Eximbank and the remaining 15
percent by the Turkish Treasury.
</P>
<P>
Boeing will deliver the first batch of the jets in July and the
last by the year 2002.
</P>
<P>
The THY made the deal in order to further promote its
competitive capacity on the world civil aviation market, a THY
official said.
</P>
<P>
With the new injection, the THY would gradually phase out some
of its aged Boeing 737-400, 37-500 and RJ-100 jetliners over the
next five years.
</P>
<P>
The THY now has a fleet of 65 aircraft. 
</P>
</TEXT>
